### isAngleBracketString() {#a596b6449296931e40cbfb38f8cb238c1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isAngleBracketString (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> &amp; StrLoc, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> &amp; EndLoc)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
This function checks if the next token is &lt;string&gt; type or arithmetic.

string that begin with character &#39;&lt;&#39; must end with character &#39;&gt;&#39;. otherwise it is arithmetics. If the function returns a &#39;true&#39; value, the End argument will be filled with the last location pointed to the &#39;&gt;&#39; character. There is a gap between the AltMacro&#39;s documentation and the single quote implementation. GCC does not fully support this feature and so we will not support it. <Link id="l04718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4718"><Highlight kind="comment">/// intended or change the macro to use the named parameters.  It is possible</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4719"><Highlight kind="comment">/// this warning will trigger when the none of the named parameters are used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4720"><Highlight kind="comment">/// and the strings like $1 are infact to simply to be passed trough unchanged.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
